{"id":41054,"description":"<div class=\"mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><p>This is a commercially guided trip led by local guide companies.. It may be possible to descend on your own.\n<\/p><p>Some of the many available guide companies:\n<\/p>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/www.imagineecuador.com\/best-canyoning-banos-ecuador\/\">Imagine Ecuador<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/www.geotoursbanios.com\/tour\/tour-canyoning-rio-blanco-level-III-banos-de-agua-santa-ecuador\/\">Geo Tours<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/canyoningecuador.com\/tours\/canyoning-rio-blanco-banos\/\">Canyoning Ecuador<\/a><\/li><\/ul>\n<meta property=\"mw:PageProp\/toc\" \/>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Approach\">Approach<\/h2><\/div>\n<p>Map shown on this page is estimated approach. The area appears to have seen some new roads, trails and properties in recent years. The approach shown here should be fine, but always ask locals about where you can park, and which approach trail to use.\n<\/p>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Descent\">Descent<\/h2><\/div>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Exit\">Exit<\/h2><\/div>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Red_tape\">Red tape<\/h2><\/div>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Beta_sites\">Beta sites<\/h2><\/div>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http:\/\/icopro.org\/canyon\/view\/id\/251\">Icopro.org<\/a> &#160;: Rio Blanco<\/li><\/ul>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Trip_reports_and_media\">Trip reports and media<\/h2><\/div>\n<style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r1062633282\">@media all and (max-width:720px){.mw-parser-output .content .thumb>div:not(.thumbinner){display:flex;justify-content:center;flex-wrap:wrap;align-content:flex-start;flex-direction:column}}body.skin-vector .mw